<subSubSection lastPageId="30" lastPageNumber="31" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,1829,2036]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1829,1856]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Palpus concave on subapicolateral surface (ch.9-1; 
<figureCitation box="[860,948,1829,1855]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="32.[151,250,1936,1961]" captionTargetBox="[166,1420,633,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[166,1420,633,1910]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURE 9. Phortica (Ashima) takehiroi Toda, sp. nov. (♂ paratype). A, Head (caudal view); B, antenna; C, palpus and prob- ocsis; D, prementum; E, abdominal sternites; F, periphallic organs (caudolateral view); G–I, phallic organs (lateral, ventrolateral and ventral views, respectively). Scale bars: 0.1 mm in B–D, F–I; 0.5 mm in A, E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884632" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884632/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Fig. 9C</figureCitation>
); abdominal sternite III widest among sternites (ch.23-1; 
<figureCitation box="[318,404,1865,1891]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="32.[151,250,1936,1961]" captionTargetBox="[166,1420,633,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[166,1420,633,1910]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURE 9. Phortica (Ashima) takehiroi Toda, sp. nov. (♂ paratype). A, Head (caudal view); B, antenna; C, palpus and prob- ocsis; D, prementum; E, abdominal sternites; F, periphallic organs (caudolateral view); G–I, phallic organs (lateral, ventrolateral and ventral views, respectively). Scale bars: 0.1 mm in B–D, F–I; 0.5 mm in A, E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884632" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884632/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Fig. 9E</figureCitation>
); sternite V with dense setulae on medial surface (ch.28-1; 
<figureCitation box="[1059,1144,1865,1891]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="32.[151,250,1936,1961]" captionTargetBox="[166,1420,633,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[166,1420,633,1910]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURE 9. Phortica (Ashima) takehiroi Toda, sp. nov. (♂ paratype). A, Head (caudal view); B, antenna; C, palpus and prob- ocsis; D, prementum; E, abdominal sternites; F, periphallic organs (caudolateral view); G–I, phallic organs (lateral, ventrolateral and ventral views, respectively). Scale bars: 0.1 mm in B–D, F–I; 0.5 mm in A, E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884632" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884632/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Fig. 9E</figureCitation>
); hypandrium asymmetric (ch.40-1; 
<figureCitation box="[259,336,1901,1927]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="32.[151,250,1936,1961]" captionTargetBox="[166,1420,633,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[166,1420,633,1910]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURE 9. Phortica (Ashima) takehiroi Toda, sp. nov. (♂ paratype). A, Head (caudal view); B, antenna; C, palpus and prob- ocsis; D, prementum; E, abdominal sternites; F, periphallic organs (caudolateral view); G–I, phallic organs (lateral, ventrolateral and ventral views, respectively). Scale bars: 0.1 mm in B–D, F–I; 0.5 mm in A, E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884632" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884632/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Fig. 9I</figureCitation>
); pregonite (
<figureCitation box="[477,564,1901,1927]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="32.[151,250,1936,1961]" captionTargetBox="[166,1420,633,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[166,1420,633,1910]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURE 9. Phortica (Ashima) takehiroi Toda, sp. nov. (♂ paratype). A, Head (caudal view); B, antenna; C, palpus and prob- ocsis; D, prementum; E, abdominal sternites; F, periphallic organs (caudolateral view); G–I, phallic organs (lateral, ventrolateral and ventral views, respectively). Scale bars: 0.1 mm in B–D, F–I; 0.5 mm in A, E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884632" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884632/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Fig. 9G</figureCitation>
) with neither basal extension (ch.49-0) nor sensilla on basal portion (ch.53-0); aedeagus without spiny ornamentation on outer membrane (ch.55-1; 
<figureCitation box="[922,1011,1937,1963]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="32.[151,250,1936,1961]" captionTargetBox="[166,1420,633,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[166,1420,633,1910]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURE 9. Phortica (Ashima) takehiroi Toda, sp. nov. (♂ paratype). A, Head (caudal view); B, antenna; C, palpus and prob- ocsis; D, prementum; E, abdominal sternites; F, periphallic organs (caudolateral view); G–I, phallic organs (lateral, ventrolateral and ventral views, respectively). Scale bars: 0.1 mm in B–D, F–I; 0.5 mm in A, E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884632" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884632/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Fig. 9G</figureCitation>
); aedeagal sheath with only 1 anterior or 1 posterior, strongly sclerotized postgonite on each side (
<figureCitation box="[819,925,1973,1999]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="32.[151,250,1936,1961]" captionTargetBox="[166,1420,633,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[166,1420,633,1910]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURE 9. Phortica (Ashima) takehiroi Toda, sp. nov. (♂ paratype). A, Head (caudal view); B, antenna; C, palpus and prob- ocsis; D, prementum; E, abdominal sternites; F, periphallic organs (caudolateral view); G–I, phallic organs (lateral, ventrolateral and ventral views, respectively). Scale bars: 0.1 mm in B–D, F–I; 0.5 mm in A, E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884632" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884632/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Fig. 9H,I</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,1829,2036]" lastBlockId="30.[151,1437,153,323]" lastPageId="30" lastPageNumber="31" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,429,2009,2036]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Shared characters.</emphasis>
Dorsomedial, tentorial apodeme &lt;3/5 basal, parallel portion of dorsolateral, tentorial apodeme (ch.1-1). Abdominal sternites III and IV wider than long (ch.22,24-1; 
<figureCitation box="[1040,1125,153,179]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="32.[151,250,1936,1961]" captionTargetBox="[166,1420,633,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[166,1420,633,1910]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURE 9. Phortica (Ashima) takehiroi Toda, sp. nov. (♂ paratype). A, Head (caudal view); B, antenna; C, palpus and prob- ocsis; D, prementum; E, abdominal sternites; F, periphallic organs (caudolateral view); G–I, phallic organs (lateral, ventrolateral and ventral views, respectively). Scale bars: 0.1 mm in B–D, F–I; 0.5 mm in A, E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884632" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884632/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Fig. 9E</figureCitation>
), with dense setulae on medial surface (ch.26,27-1; 
<figureCitation box="[432,518,189,215]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="32.[151,250,1936,1961]" captionTargetBox="[166,1420,633,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[166,1420,633,1910]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURE 9. Phortica (Ashima) takehiroi Toda, sp. nov. (♂ paratype). A, Head (caudal view); B, antenna; C, palpus and prob- ocsis; D, prementum; E, abdominal sternites; F, periphallic organs (caudolateral view); G–I, phallic organs (lateral, ventrolateral and ventral views, respectively). Scale bars: 0.1 mm in B–D, F–I; 0.5 mm in A, E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884632" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884632/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Fig. 9E</figureCitation>
). Setae on and/or near ventral margin of epandrium not denser than those on other portions (ch.32-0; 
<figureCitation box="[363,449,225,251]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="32.[151,250,1936,1961]" captionTargetBox="[166,1420,633,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[166,1420,633,1910]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURE 9. Phortica (Ashima) takehiroi Toda, sp. nov. (♂ paratype). A, Head (caudal view); B, antenna; C, palpus and prob- ocsis; D, prementum; E, abdominal sternites; F, periphallic organs (caudolateral view); G–I, phallic organs (lateral, ventrolateral and ventral views, respectively). Scale bars: 0.1 mm in B–D, F–I; 0.5 mm in A, E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884632" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884632/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Fig. 9F</figureCitation>
). Surstylus with peg-like teeth (ch.37-0). Pregonite with sensilla on submedial portion (ch.52-1). Sclerotized, posterior postgonites on aedeagal sheath medially separated from each other (ch.66-0).
</paragraph>
